You say there's no catch. But how do you explain the "Fair Use Policy"? In your package, you mention "Video Streaming (YouTube, Netflix) and File Sharing. But in your "Fair Use Policy" mentions that if we use (P2P) file sharing software or streaming video services we are more likely to break the policy. Is this just the usual false advertisement and screw people over in the fine print?

Good Day Joshua, we do not 'screw people over in the fine print'; if you would like to discuss further perhaps you should visit us in Providence where the technical people will be happy to explain to you how the Fair Use Policy works. If you apply logic to an Unlimited package, it is obvious that one person could take everything at the expense of the others. That is why every telco around the world implements Fair Use Policies. Since Seychelles is part of the global economy, we will do the same and if we are all fair to each other, and respect each other's right to use the internet, then everything will be fine. This is how Unlimited works. Thanks for your comment and we look forward to you visit. Thanks. Intelvision Team.

What u mean by sim cards

What exactly is a SIM card? You know, the little piece of plastic found in the metal pullout on the right side of your iPhone or cellular iPad? The short answer: it's a Subscriber Identity Module, a small circuit board in most modern phones to communicate with your carrier. Practically speaking, it is a middleman between two pieces of hardware: the phone's baseband chip, and your carrier's cell towers, allowing the two to communicate.

Intelvision advertises Olympics coverage on two channels from 4pm-7am. The two channels are constantly changing between BBC, Bein and some arabic channel which makes it hard to believe that there has been any official subscription to any channel on their part. As we speak they are showing a Celtic game that has nothing to do with the Olympics. Most of the afternoon and night we have seen some old replays from three days ago and some completely unrelated stuff. Yesterday and the day before we were treated with US baseball. Very little live coverage of actual olympics and it is always obviously taken from the scrap channels of either bein or god knows what else. Often the signal goes completely off and a white screen appears with the sign "our technical team are working on the issue", whch frankly sounds more like a joke than anything else. I have called twice to make a complaint, my wife three times. Each time we get bounced off. Each time nothing gets done, all we achieve is getting frustrated at someone on the phone who keeps repeating that there is an issue "that has just come up". NO it has not just come up, it has been going on throughout the entire Olympics. The Intelvision package including sports channels is insanely expensive. And the most important sports event of the year does not work. This is misleading advertisement and it is frankly disgraceful.

Marco, we try to meet the tastes of the majority. In Seychelles, the most popular sport by far, is football.  We try to find a balance by airing some of the Olympics, and clearly this has created an expectation which in your opinion, we have not met. We can only apologize. In our defense and by no means as an excuse, we are a 100% local operator ie we only serve Seychelles. We do not buy content in volumes and then sell across multiple geographies. This means we have to really work hard to offer shows at reasonable prices to all our customers. Thanks for your support and we will try to address some of your frustrations with our call center.
